<div class="pizza-card">
    <h2>Layout Implementation</h2>
    <p>Here's how layouts are implemented in Blazor:</p>

    <h3>1. Layout Component Structure</h3>
    <pre><code>@@inherits LayoutComponentBase

&lt;header&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Blazing Pizza&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;

&lt;nav&gt;
    &lt;a href="Pizzas"&gt;Browse Pizzas&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/nav&gt;

@@Body

&lt;footer&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;¬© Blazing Pizzas 2024&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/footer&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>2. Using Layouts in Components</h3>
    <pre><code>@@page "/admin"
@@layout AdminLayout

&lt;h1&gt;Admin Dashboard&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This content appears in the @@Body section&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>

    <h3>3. Default Layout Configuration</h3>
    <pre><code>&lt;Router AppAssembly="@@typeof(Program).Assembly"&gt;
    &lt;Found Context="routeData"&gt;
        &lt;RouteView RouteData="@@routeData" 
                   DefaultLayout="@@typeof(MainLayout)" /&gt;
    &lt;/Found&gt;
&lt;/Router&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<div class="pizza-card">
    <h2>Layout Benefits</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Consistency:</strong> All pages share common UI elements</li>
        <li><strong>Maintainability:</strong> Update layout once, affects all pages</li>
        <li><strong>Flexibility:</strong> Different layouts for different page types</li>
        <li><strong>Reusability:</strong> Layouts can be shared across components</li>
        <li><strong>Separation of Concerns:</strong> Layout logic separate from page content</li>
    </ul>
</div>

